IHS Cuts 2011 U.S. Auto Sales Forecast to 12.5 Million

-- B y   J o s h u a   A r m s t r o n g
-- 
2011-08-11T19:39:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/ihs-cuts-2011-u-s-auto-sales-forecast-200-000-units-to-12-5-million.html
IHS Automotive reduced its estimate
for U.S. auto sales in 2011 by 200,000 units to 12.5 million
light vehicles, analyst  Rebecca Lindland  said in a phone
interview.  IHS cut its estimate for 2012 deliveries in the U.S. to
13.5 million vehicles, from 14.7 million, Lindland said. The
Lexington, Massachusetts-based researcher also lowered its
estimate for light-vehicle sales in 2013 to 15 million, from
15.5 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Armstrong in Detroit at 
 jarmstrong39@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  